Anh - Anh
psilocybin
[ˌsʌɪlə(ʊ)'sʌɪbɪn]
■ noun Chemistry a hallucinogenic compound of the alkaloid class, found in the liberty cap and related toadstools.
Origin
1950s: from mod. L. Psilocybe (genus name), from Gk psilos 'bald' + kubē 'head'.

sentences.en: The “magic” mushroom contains psilocybin, a hallucinogenic substance.
sentences.vi: Nấm "ma thuật" chứa psilocybin, một chất gây ảo giác.
